<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05039m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05039m">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05039m"> 39(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> brother = cousin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">At first it was maintained that the brothers and sisters of Jesus referred to in the Gospels were children of Joseph by a former marriage; subsequently, it was held that Joseph also lived in perpetual virginity; finally, <mark>the brothers of Jesus were transformed into his cousins</mark>, and to affirm otherwise was declared to be a blasphemous impiety. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="TMOG" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TMOG"><cite title="source">The Mother of God</cite></a>, (1918) 17-8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
